The Right to Know Campaign has welcomed Nomvuyo Mhlakaza and Aaron Tshidzumba resignations. JOHANNESBURG - The Right to Know Campaign has welcomed the resignation of two South African Broadcasting Corporation (SABC) board members.Nomvuyo Mhlakaza and Aaron Tshidzumba tendered their resignations over the weekend.That means chairperson Mbulaheni Magubhe is now the only non-executive member left.The inquiry into the public broadcaster s board officially started today. The ad hoc committee for the inquiry was appointed by the National Assembly and has until January to decide on the board s future.The Right to Know Campaign s Micah Reddy said: It doesn t come as a total surprise that they would resign, the writing on the wall has been there for a long time and it would be almost impossible for the parliamentary portfolio committee that is looking into the board not to dissolve the board after this. (Edited by Winnie Theletsane)